1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,851
CHAPTER TWELVE USE GOALS TO HELP YOU GROW Every bit of human progress—our inventions,

2
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:18,851
big and little, our medical discoveries, our engineering triumphs, our business successes—were first visualized before they became realities.

3
00:00:19,440 --> 00:00:28,931
Baby moons circle the Earth not because of accidental discoveries, but because scientists set conquer space as a goal.

4
00:00:29,440 --> 00:00:32,370
A goal is an objective, a purpose.

5
00:00:32,641 --> 00:00:36,931
A goal is more than a dream, it's a dream being acted upon.

6
00:00:37,281 --> 00:00:41,091
A goal is more than a hazy, oh, I wish I could.

7
00:00:41,281 --> 00:00:45,091
A goal is a clear, this is what I'm working toward.

8
00:00:45,921 --> 00:00:51,171
Nothing happens, no forward steps are taken, until a goal is established.

9
00:00:51,441 --> 00:00:55,330
Without goals, individuals just wander through life.

10
00:00:55,441 --> 00:01:00,531
They stumble along, never knowing where they are going, so they never get anywhere.

11
00:01:01,441 --> 00:01:05,811
Goals are as essential to success as air is to life.

12
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:09,410
No one ever stumbles into success without a goal.

13
00:01:09,601 --> 00:01:11,731
No one ever lives without air.

14
00:01:11,841 --> 00:01:14,611
Get a clear fix on where you want to go.

15
00:01:15,361 --> 00:01:27,731
Dave Mahoney rose from a low-paying job in the mailroom of an advertising agency to an agency vice president at 27 and president of the Good Humor company at 33.

16
00:01:28,161 --> 00:01:30,451
This is what he says about goals.

17
00:01:30,641 --> 00:01:36,690
The important thing is not where you were or where you are, but where you want to get.

18
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:42,770
The Progressive Corporation plans company goals 10 to 15 years ahead.

19
00:01:43,121 --> 00:01:50,050
Executives who manage leading businesses must ask, where do we want our company to be ten years from now?

20
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:53,011
Then they gauge their efforts accordingly.

21
00:01:53,281 --> 00:02:00,451
New plant capacity is built not for today's needs, but rather for needs five to ten years in the future.

22
00:02:00,881 --> 00:02:06,291
Research is undertaken to develop products that won't appear for a decade or longer.

23
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:11,251
The modern corporation does not leave its future to chance, should you.

24
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:16,611
Each of us can learn a precious lesson from the forward-looking business.

25
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:20,691
We can and should plan at least ten years ahead.

26
00:02:21,201 --> 00:02:26,291
You must form an image now of the person you want to be ten years from now,

27
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,451
if you are to become that image.

28
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,291
This is a critical thought.

29
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:37,251
Just as the business that neglects to plan ahead will be just another business if it even survives,

30
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:45,411
the individual who fails to set long-range goals will most certainly be just another person lost in life's shuffle.

31
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:48,210
Without goals, we cannot grow.

32
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:49,011
Let me share with you an example of why we must have long-run goals to achieve real success.
